Class Wall

  • java.lang.Object

  • public class Wall
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the walls of the house which are rectangular in shape.

    • Field Detail

      • wallType

        private char wallType
        This tells the type of the wall. The wall type is 'w' if the wall is constructed along the width of the house. The wall type is 'l' if the wall is constructed along the length of the house. The wall type is 'f' or 'c' if the wall represents the floor or the ceiling respectively. However, you do not need to worry much about it. It is made sure that in the constructor, a correct value is passed

      • wallLength

        private int wallLength
        This is the length of the wall which will be assigned depending upon the wallType. If the wallType is 'w', then the wallLength is the roomWidth. If the wallType is 'l' then the wallLength is the roomLength. Otherwise the wallLength is the roomLength itself.

      • wallWidth

        private int wallWidth
        The wallWidth is height of the home if wallType is 'w' or 'l' and is the roomWidth when wallType is 'f' or 'c'.

      • wallState

        private char wallState
        This denotes the wallState of the wall. It can take values 'g' (good) or 'b' (bad).

    • Constructor Detail

      • Wall

        public Wall(char wallType,
            boolean isRaining,
            int roomWidth,
            int roomLength)
        Constructor for objects of class Wall
        Parameters:
        wallType - Initialises the wallType by the given value.
        isRaining - isRaining is a boolean variable which is used to initialise the wallState of the Wall. If it is raining, i.e. if isRaining is true, then wallState must be assigned 'b' (bad) otherwise, it must be assigned 'g' (good) So, a wall is said to be good if it is in good state and bad if it is in bad state
        roomWidth - denotes the width of the room containing that wall
        roomLength - denotes the length of the room containing that wall Note: wallWidth and wallLength should be initialised depending on the wallType
